  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Application\'s Focus**\n\nI\'m solidifying the project\'s core. The goal is a mobile-first web app, specifically for ESP32 control via Wi-Fi, using React. This means it must be a single-page app, served directly from the ESP32\'s flash. The interface needs to be intuitive for managing various IoT devices.\n\n\n**Refining the UI/UX**\n\nI\'m now focusing on UI/UX considerations. The app should be minimalist, modern, and reactive. Memory constraints on the ESP32 are key, so I\'m thinking how to optimize the design for minimal footprint. A key requirement is the ability for multiple ESP32 devices to discover and interact with each other on the local network within the app. I can simulate the interface beautifully, and also generate C++/Arduino code.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 113882875
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
