  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Local Storage Access**\n\nI\'ve successfully created the data presets. Now, I\'m focusing on how the browser, running on the ESP32\'s WiFi, will communicate with local storage. Specifically, when served from the ESP32, my fetches need to target local resources.\n\n\n**Addressing Cross-Node Control**\n\nI\'ve determined the approach for multi-node control. Since the React app and target ESP32 share the same IP, direct requests like `http://192.168.4.15/api/toggle` are feasible. To sidestep potential CORS issues in Spain or Brazil, I\'ll ensure the firmware includes `httpServer.enableCORS()` or explicit headers. I\'m excited about how this will streamline multi-node control from the browser. Next, I\'m starting work on `/src/components/ESP32Visualizer.tsx`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 18
      nanos: 928688775
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
