  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Generating Pin Configuration Code**\n\nI\'ve generated the pin configuration code, and I\'m very pleased with the results. It\'s beautiful, aligns perfectly with all the user\'s requirements, and is responsive, with a mobile-first design. I\'m now moving on to the `/src/components/NodeMonitor.tsx` component.\n\n\n**Defining NodeMonitor Functionality**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the functionality of the `NodeMonitor`. I\'ve outlined the core features: it will display a list of discovered ESP32 nodes, showing their hostname, IP address, RSSI, and role. Furthermore, I\'ve specified a key feature: active pin visualization. Users can see and control other ESP32 devices directly from the list, simulating pin changes via REST API requests. I\'m also including manual node addition via IP and Host.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
