    thinking: "**Analyzing the \"Sleek Interface\"**\n\nI\'m now diving into the \"Sleek Interface\" design\'s HTML to extract crucial visual elements. Specifically, I\'m noting the background color (`#090A0D`) and starting to examine the mockup device\'s dimensions. I\'ll need to parse the device model\'s visual properties, to accurately generate and implement this design concept.\n\n\n**Refining the Smartphone Wrapper**\n\nI\'ve been analyzing the smartphone wrapper\'s design elements in `App.tsx` and refining the visual aspects. I\'ve pinpointed the key design components, including background, border, shadow, and rounded corners, to optimize the layout. I\'m focusing on incorporating a vibrant cyan color for active states and transitioning from the original neutral tones to the richer colors such as `#1C1F2B`, `#171A24`, and `#252936`. I\'m going for consistent and aesthetically pleasing UI elements!\n\n\n**Aligning Visual Components**\n\nI\'m now integrating the visual elements of `ESP32Visualizer.tsx` with the Sleek Interface. I\'m updating the component styles to match the new theme, specifically the outer board background, core chip body, and the left/right rail. I\'m updating `PinController` to use `bg-[#1C1F2B]` and the inner buttons to match the sleek design. The new styling will be applied across the board for visual consistency.\n\n\n**Updating UI Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now in the process of applying the \"Sleek Interface\" theme\'s color palette to components, starting with UI element colors and borders. I\'m focusing on consistency: replacing `bg-blue-600` with `bg-cyan-600` for active states and applying cyan accents where blue was previously used. I\'ve analyzed `NodeMonitor`\'s peer node lists and am updating the cards to match their aesthetic. Next, I\'ll update `FirmwareExporter` and `LogConsole`. I\'m starting by refining `App.tsx` navigation.\n\n\n**Refining Navigation Styles**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the navigation bar\'s visual style within `App.tsx`. I\'m replacing the existing class names with new ones. I\'m taking the Sleek Theme template\'s nav bar into consideration. I will replace the current bottom navigation elements with the class `h-20 w-full bg-[#1A1D27] border-t border-white/5 px-8 flex justify-between items-center`. I\'m updating the styling for selected states as well. I\'ll ensure consistent application of the theme\'s colors and fonts.\n\n\n**Implementing Tab Navigation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the tab navigation styling within `App.tsx`, and planning to transform it into the Sleek Interface style. I\'m targeting the `bg-[#1A1D27]` and `border-t border-white/5` classes. The original nav bar has four items: Controls, Mesh, C++ Code, and Maker IA. I\'m also preparing to change the parent background to `#090A0D` and update the mockup background to `#12141C` with border `#252833`.\n\n\n**Adjusting Component Styles**\n\nI\'m now refining the visual styling, focusing on the device frame and network banner. I\'m updating the `div` element to enhance its visual appeal. The `wifiSettings` banner styling has been updated to use the appropriate colors and effects, which now uses `bg-[#1C1F2B]` and `border border-white/5`. I\'m going through the different changes.\n\n\n"
