  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Modularization Options**\n\nI\'m evaluating the best way to integrate OTA update functionality. I\'m leaning toward creating a dedicated component, likely `/src/components/OtaUpdate.tsx`, to maintain modularity as per React best practices. I\'m trying to avoid unnecessary consolidation, and the potential complexity warrants a separate module. I\'m focusing on simplicity and maintainability here.\n\n\n**Designing the OTA Update Section**\n\nI\'m now fully committed to a dedicated `/src/components/OtaUpdate.tsx` component. The design phase focuses on visual appeal and usability. I\'m prioritizing an intuitive file upload area, with drag-and-drop and click-to-select functionality, accepting `.bin` files or placeholders. It will have clear visual feedback and a custom upload box, all while maintaining the project\'s aesthetic with the consistent theme. The plan is to create an aesthetically pleasing and user-friendly interaction.\n\n\n**Simulating Upload Progress**\n\nI\'m now creating a dynamic progress simulation within the OTA component. Upon file selection, I\'ll display the file details and an \"Iniciar Atualiza\303\247\303\243o\" button. I\'m focusing on a real-time progress bar, animated with phases mirroring an ESP32 OTA upload (connection, data transmission, MD5 validation, finalization). The serial terminal will display log messages to track progress. Status indicators (progress bar, percentage, estimated time, speed) will also be included in the UI. Upon completion, a success message will appear.\n\n\n"
